<h2 id="integration-ecosystem">🔌 Integration Ecosystem</h2>

PushPress maintains an open philosophy toward integrations. The platform connects natively with major accounting software, marketing tools, and fitness-specific applications. More importantly, full API access means developers can build custom connections without hitting artificial walls.

Common PushPress integrations our team has deployed include QuickBooks for accounting automation, ActiveCampaign for email marketing, and custom Airtable dashboards for franchise reporting. These connections work reliably and update in real-time through well-documented APIs.

Wodify's integration ecosystem has expanded but remains more controlled. The platform offers connections to popular tools like Zapier and select accounting packages, but custom development requires enterprise agreements or workarounds through their more limited public API. For operators who view their tech stack as interconnected systems rather than isolated tools, this limitation proves frustrating.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Map your ideal tech stack before selecting a gym management platform. If you need data flowing between your CRM, accounting software, scheduling tools, and member management system, PushPress's open architecture provides the foundation. If your needs stay within the gym management platform itself, Wodify's native features might suffice.
</div>

<h2 id="support-onboarding">📞 Support and Onboarding</h2>

Both platforms provide adequate support for single-location operators. Response times average under 24 hours for standard tickets, and both offer phone support during business hours. The differences emerge with complex multi-location issues or technical integration questions.

PushPress assigns dedicated success managers to multi-location accounts and provides direct access to technical staff for API-related questions. Our team has resolved complex billing reconciliation issues through screen-shares with PushPress engineers—a level of access that matters when real money discrepancies surface.

Wodify's support operates more traditionally. Standard support handles most issues competently, but escalations for technical problems sometimes stall in queues. For operators who expect their software vendors to operate as partners rather than vendors, the support model differences matter.

<h2 id="final-verdict">🏆 Final Verdict</h2>

PushPress earns our recommendation for CrossFit operators planning any growth beyond a single location. The platform's transparent pricing, open architecture, and operational focus align with how successful gym businesses actually scale. The savings compound—both in direct costs and in administrative hours recovered from manual reporting and reconciliation.

